            <title>[QPID-928] Test org.apache.qpid.test.unit.client.connection.ConnectionCloseTest intermittently failing </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-928</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This test is failing because more than 10 threads are still running immediately after the 500 connections are closed. It appears that those threads are Mina threads waiting on a selector key. Those threads are eventually notified if the main thread waits before checking for potential spurious threads. &lt;br/&gt;
As the threshold (currently set to 10) is arbitrary, I would suggest that we wait 1s before making the check that should leave all type of hardware enough time to cleanup, we would then use a 0 threshold i.e. no spurious thread would be tolerated.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
